Citations
Date: 0/0/1949
Source: High Country Days
Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 102
Edition:
Quote: The tip, a small pen capable of holding 10 or 12 sheep, was situated a foot or so above and partly overhanging the dip. ... with the aid of a lever it could be tipped and the sheep sent slithering into the dip below. The decoy pen was so situated that two or three sheep placed in itdecoyed others onto the tip.
